From c3b06802c8dc9245f9802ab0296920966eb6ca7b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 08:00:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] BCanvas uniform scale + RGraphics viewport-scale hook
 (render-half of visual-viewport zoom)

BCanvas gains a uniform Scale(float) composed with its _translation (draws map
point -> point*scale + translation through the two central Translate helpers, with
scalar device dimensions scaled too; Save/Restore-scoped; byte-identical at scale 1).
RGraphics gains virtual PushViewportScale(float)/PopViewportScale() (default no-op)
so a backend can apply a document-root viewport zoom after the device-space viewport
clip. Test: 'BCanvas scales draws about the origin'; all existing tests pass.
---
 Broiler.Graphics.Tests/BitmapCanvasTests.cs | 22 ++++++++
 Broiler.Graphics/Adapters/RGraphics.cs      |  8 +++
 Broiler.Graphics/Rendering/BCanvas.cs       | 56 +++++++++++++--------
 3 files changed, 65 insertions(+), 21 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Broiler.Graphics.Tests/BitmapCanvasTests.cs b/Broiler.Graphics.Tests/BitmapCanvasTests.cs
